translated:
Claes Dan Osvald was a physician at the county hospital in Strömstad. He was born on November 18th, 1898 in Annelöv, Malmöhus County, the first child of N. P. Svensson and Maria Danielsson. He married Iniger Elimä in 1931 and they had two children, Gunilla born in 1933 and Göran born in 1935. 

Claes obtained a degree in medicine from Lund University in 1922, and later his license in 1926. He worked as a research assistant at the physiology institute in Lund from 1922 to 1923, and as a physician at Vadstena Hospital in 1926. He also worked as an assistant physician and temporary chief physician at various hospitals in Landskrona, Malmö, Norrköping, and Sabbatsberg, and was also a naval physician in Fikres (1927). He became a chief physician at the county hospital in Alingsås in 1938 and later served as the second physician in the medical department at Sabbatsberg hospital in the same year, and finally as a physician at the county hospital in Strömstad from 1941.
